# Skip tests in dev

During normal local development work, **do not run tests** unless the user explicitly asks (e.g. "run tests", "fix CI", "add tests").

## Do not run

- `make test`, or `make check` when it would invoke tests
- `uv run pytest`, `pytest -m postgres`
- `npm run test`, `npm run test:watch`, `npm run e2e`
- Playwright or other Docker-based test invocations

## Still allowed

- `ruff check`, `make lint-check`, `npm run lint`, `npm run build`
- Reading existing test files for context

## Writing tests

Add or change tests only when the user requests them.

## When tests are required

Run the test suite when the user explicitly asks, when fixing CI failures, or when the task is specifically about tests.

CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) is the canonical test runner on pull requests.
